AGI -&nbsp;Polmonitis bilateral: is what demonstrated the tac of control to which Pope Francis was subjected in the afternoon of today. The medical bulletin issued by the Vatican shows a worsening of the situation and the change of care, the third in five days>, provides a more complex treatment.
"Polymicrobial infection, insorted on a framework of bronchiectasia and bronchitis asmatiform, and which demanded the use of antibiotic cortisonic therapy, makes therapeutic treatment more complex", says the director of the press room of the Holy See Matteo Bruni. "The tac thorax of control to which the Holy Father was subjected this afternoon, prescribed by the Vatican health team and the medical one of the Polyclinic Foundation 'A. Gemelli' - it is explained -, has demonstrated the occurrence of a bilateral pneumonia that has requested further pharmacological therapy >".
<div </div
Pope Francis nevertheless "is in a good mood". This morning she received the Eucharist and, during the day, she alternated the rest of prayer and reading texts. "Thank you for the closeness you feel at this moment and asks, with gratitude, that you continue to pray for him." So a worsening of health conditions, made even more alarming especially for the age of the Pope. All commitments have been cancelled today. It remains only to decide for the Angelus on Sunday.&nbsp;
